etymologies: early 18th century (in an earlier sense). From post-classical Latin summatorius from summat-, past participial stem of summare + classical Latin -ōrius

definitions: Concerning, involving, or relating to summation. Somewhat rare.

Designating an arithmetic function whose value at a given integer n is the sum of the values of another arithmetic function when evaluated at every element of its domain that is less than or equal to n.
